summary: "What do you know of my heart, priestess? What do you know of my sister?"
body:
“What do you know of my heart, priestess? What do you know of my sister?”

– Jon equating Arya with his heart, ADWD

Whether one ships Jon/Arya romantically, adores their dynamic as the closest of siblings, or has no feeling about them at all, there should be no denying that in-universe Jon considers his heart and Arya Stark to be one and the same. Not only does he outright say exactly that, his heart is often mentioned in relation to her throughout ADWD. Even in the showverse Sansa mentions how much more Jon loves Arya than he could ever love her by bringing up Jon’s heart. In fact, if Jonrya happened on the show, Sansa would clearly ship it.

summary: You don’t know how many times I had to deal with Dany stans who used Sansa smiling while watching her abuser being eaten alive...
body: You don’t know how many times I had to deal with Dany stans who used Sansa smiling while watching her abuser being eaten alive as proof that she is going dark. The fact that I’m now seeing Sansa accounts doing the exact same thing to Daenerys is just really disappointing. The fact that anyone would sympathize more with completely irredeemable abusers than with the victims of that abuse is just absurd to me. Both of these men received what was coming for them, and both Sansa and Daenerys had the right to be happy about what happened.

summary: The mare whickered softly as Jon Snow tightened the cinch. "Easy, sweet lady," he said in a soft voice, quieting her with a...
caption:
The mare whickered softly as Jon Snow tightened the cinch. “Easy, sweet lady,” he said in a soft voice, quieting her with a touch. Wind whispered through the stable, a cold dead breath on his face, but Jon paid it no mind. He strapped his roll to the saddle, his scarred fingers stiff and clumsy. “Ghost,” he called softly, “to me.” And the wolf was there, eyes like embers.

—A Game of Thrones - Jon IX

¡THIS QUOTE! 

I have so many things to say about this quote! Here is a summary:

  • Jon Snow, the guy who is supposed to like the warrior woman type, whispered to his mare “Easy, sweet lady”. He could’ve said “Easy, girl”, but he said: “Easy, sweet lady”. Oh Jon, you are such a romantic dork.  
  • Lady is also the name of Sansa’s direwolf.    
  • Lady and Ghost are mentioned together and linked in many passages of the Books. I love it.
  • At this point Lady is dead, so she is literally a ghost.
  • Later in the Books Jon also dies. So we have a direwolf with a dead master and a master with a dead direwolf.
  • And guess who is the female character that is called ‘sweet lady’ the most? Yes, the answer is Sansa. 

Art: ASoIaF - Jon Snow by Manweri
